# =============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES — Quantity Measurement Frontend (Vite + React)
# =============================================================================
#
# HOW ENV VARS WORK IN VITE:
#   - Variables MUST be prefixed with VITE_ to be exposed to the browser bundle.
#   - They are embedded at BUILD TIME (not runtime). Changing them after build
#     has no effect — you must rebuild.
#   - Access them in code via: src/config/env.js (never import.meta.env directly)
#
# FILE LOADING ORDER (Vite reads these in order, later files win):
#   .env              → always loaded — commit this with safe defaults
#   .env.local        → always loaded — NEVER commit (add to .gitignore)
#   .env.development  → loaded when running `vite` (dev mode)
#   .env.production   → loaded when running `vite build`
#
# To customise locally: copy the variable(s) you want to override into a new
# .env.local file (git-ignored) and set your values there.
#
# =============================================================================
# WHERE TO SET VARIABLES — DECISION GUIDE
# =============================================================================
#
#  Environment      | Where to set                          | Why
# ──────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────
#  Local dev        | .env.local (git-ignored)              | Personal overrides
#  Shared defaults  | .env (this file, committed)           | Team baseline
#  Production build | CI/CD pipeline OS env vars            | Injected at build time
#  Docker           | docker run -e VITE_API_URL=...        | Runtime injection
#  Kubernetes       | ConfigMap + Secret → Pod env vars     | Per-environment config
#
# FOR CI/CD (GitHub Actions example):
#   env:
#     VITE_API_URL: ${{ secrets.PROD_API_URL }}
#   run: npm run build
#
# =============================================================================
# VARIABLES
# =============================================================================

# The base URL of your Spring Boot backend (no trailing slash).
# In production/staging you MUST override this via CI/CD or .env.local —
# the default below is for local development only.
#
# Examples:
#   Local dev:   http://localhost:8080
#   Docker:      http://backend:8080   (service name in docker-compose)
#   Production:  https://api.yourdomain.com
#
VITE_API_URL=
